# Public Debt and Government Finances in South Africa

## Overview

This project demonstrates the use of Python (Pandas and NumPy) for basic data handling, exploration, and preparation in an applied economics research context.

The project forms part of a broader empirical investigation into the impact of public debt on government finances in South Africa. Python was used to import, inspect, organise, and prepare macroeconomic data before conducting econometric analysis in EViews.

## Objective

To prepare and analyse macroeconomic data related to public debt, government finances, unemployment etc, and to investigate their relationships using econometric techniques.

## Tools Used

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* EViews
* Excel

## Python Tasks Performed

# The Python component of this project focused on:

* Importing Excel datasets
* Inspecting data 
* Reviewing data structure  
* Generating summary statistics 
* Filtering observations
* Setting and managing indexes
* Creating a tax-to-debt ratio variable
* Preparing data for econometric analysis



# Econometric Analysis

The prepared data was subsequently analysed in EViews using regression techniques to examine:

* Public sector wage bill and public debt
* Debt-service costs and government expenditure
* Unemployment and revenue sustainability

# The statistical modelling and econometric interpretation were conducted in EViews, while Python was used for data preparation and exploratory analysis.


